<br />

<br />
I didnt see the faction bar move but I never see it move anyhow
<br />
- I rely on the chat log to tell me how much faction I got  (none, slight, regular, great)
<br />

<br />

<br />
Tanaris has a repeatable quest
<br />
<a href="http://www.thottbot.com/index.cgi?q=1333" target="_blank">http://www.thottbot.com/index.cgi?q=1333</a>
<br />

<br />
I did WaterBandits  for 2 levels
<br />
(to raise 100g mount money)
<br />

<br />
without doing any elite Tanaris quests, I got close to honored with Gadgetzan after turning in over 300 Waterskins  (quest asks for 5)
<br />

<br />
Waterskins are *vastly* more abundant than morrowgrain
<br />

<br />
I didnt test if that quest would keep giving faction beyond honored but I would assume all repeatable quests do (assuming they are not a grey con)
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
I currently have my sights on the <span style="font-weight: bold">FrostSabre</span> quest for a tiger mount
<br />

<br />
its unfortunately, an "alliance only" quest in Winterspring (sorry Horde)
<br />

<br />
the repeatable quest cannot be accessed until you are level 58
<br />
(I scouted it out at level 56)
<br />

